<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Spores 7.8-9.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.9-5.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, Q = 1.6-1.8, elongated-ellipsoid in face view, in profile flattened on one side, pale brown in water, darker brown in 5% KOH, smooth, with or without 1-2 guttules, germ pore indistinct, approximately 1.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diam. Basidia 26-34 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.3-9.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, clavate, hyaline, 4- or 2-spored. Pseudoparaphyses abundant and regular distribution. Pleurocystidia 59-83 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-20 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, abundant, utriform with broadly obtuse apex, slightly thick-walled, glabrous or covered by irregular deposits, base tapering to a long stipe. Cheilocystidia 37-56 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9.8-17 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, utriform to fusoid with obtuse apex, base tapering to a short stipe. Caulocystidia 29-61 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-22 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, caespitose, various, utriform, fusoid or utriform with abrupt narrow neck terminating in a capitellum, base tapering to a long or short stipe. Trama of gills irregular. Pileipellis a 1-2-cell-deep layer of vesiculose cells, up to 61 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, covered by a 1-cell-deep layer of periclinal hyphae which are approximately 3.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diam and covered by scattered and irregular deposition dissolving in 5% KOH. Clamps present.
</paragraph>
